  "2026-06-27T22:42:32.701Z",codex-gpt5,"Second review fix evidence for PR #391: addressed current-head Gemini, CodeRabbit, and cubic feedback by making generated starter tests assert ext.deactivate() results with assertExtensionDeactivated(teardown) at the end of successful try blocks, while keeping finally blocks for fallback cleanup only via if (!deactivated) await ext.deactivate(); this avoids masking primary assertion failures while still detecting teardown regressions. Also tightened scaffold tests to assert the generated try/finally cleanup shape and teardown assertion. Verification after this fix: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/extensions/extension-command.spec.ts passed 111/111; node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/extensions/extension-scaffold-define-guidance.spec.ts passed 26/26; pnpm typecheck passed; pnpm lint passed; pnpm quality:static passed; git diff --check passed; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed 256 files / 5138 tests with 100% statements, 100% branches, 100% functions, and 100% lines; rebuilt manual temp smoke at /tmp/tmp.vWMdOkZsal passed pm init, package init, install, package doctor ok with zero warnings, starter command JSON invocation, generated package npm run typecheck, and generated package npm test 2/2; pnpm contracts:check passed; pnpm security:scan reported no credential-like secrets; pnpm audit --audit-level moderate reported no known vulnerabilities; Sentry/telemetry gate passed with critical=0 high=0 total=0 and telemetry finish_error_rate_pct=0.75 failures_without_error_code_rows=0; pnpm changelog:pm:check used pm-changelog 2026.6.27 and left CHANGELOG.md unchanged at item_count=1363; pm test pm-92if --run --progress passed all 10 linked tests."
