  "2026-06-28T07:36:57.975Z",codex-gpt5,"Review response 2026-06-28 for PR #394 final Sentry typing feedback: evaluated Gemini Code Assist suggestion to change SentryPayload back to Record<string, any>; did not introduce any because repo policy forbids it and typecheck already passed. Instead typed the test hook payloads against installed @sentry/node Event and Breadcrumb API types, separating beforeSend/beforeSendTransaction event payloads from beforeBreadcrumb breadcrumb payloads. Evidence: read installed @sentry/node/@sentry/core type exports; node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/core/sentry/sentry-helpers.spec.ts passed 40 tests; pnpm typecheck passed; pnpm lint passed including static quality; git diff --check passed; grep found no Record<string, any>, : any, as any, <any>, Array<any>, or stale SentryPayload in the edited test file."
  "2026-06-28T07:46:01.580Z",codex-gpt5,"PR #394 ready-to-merge evidence 2026-06-28: current head b410e45b has all GitHub checks green (Build foundation, Docs and Skills, Gates compat/coverage/static/smokes/typecheck, Runtime smoke Ubuntu Node 22/24, macOS Node 24, Windows Node 24, CodeQL Analyze/CodeQL, CodeFactor, CodeRabbit, Hound, Sourcery, cubic, and codecov/patch). Review loop evidence: CodeRabbit and cubic slice-boundary findings addressed in 7cee944; Gemini unused-contract finding addressed in 116081df; Gemini SentryPayload typing finding addressed in b410e45b using installed @sentry/node Event/Breadcrumb types without any. Latest Gemini review on b410e45b reports no comments to address; CodeRabbit full review finished; cubic green; Sourcery green; Codex GitHub connector remains unavailable because the repository is not connected to a Codex cloud account. Outdated Gemini review threads were resolved after verification because they are superseded by current-head commits."
  "2026-06-28T08:04:09.891Z",codex-gpt5,"Review response 2026-06-28 for PR #394 Gemini shared-contract mutability feedback: internal SDK option contract helper groups are now readonly, and each exported option-contract array receives cloned contract objects so accidental runtime mutation of one export cannot leak into list/search/aggregate/dedupe/update-many/close-many siblings while preserving the public mutable ToolOptionFlagContract[] export shape. Added tests/unit/sdk/tool-option-contracts.spec.ts to mutate representative exported status contracts and assert the sibling arrays remain isolated. Evidence after the fix: pm linked test node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/sdk/tool-option-contracts.spec.ts tests/unit/commands/contracts-command.spec.ts tests/unit/sdk/sdk-index.spec.ts passed 3 files / 148 tests in sandboxed linked-test context; full coverage node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed 257 files / 5139 tests with 100% statements, branches, functions, and lines; pnpm typecheck passed; pnpm lint passed with static quality gate passed and duplicate count unchanged at 26 known clones / 809 TS lines; pnpm quality:static passed; pnpm contracts:check passed; pnpm security:scan found no credential-like secrets; pnpm audit --audit-level moderate found no known vulnerabilities; pnpm changelog:pm:check used pm-changelog 2026.6.27 and left CHANGELOG.md unchanged with item_count=1363; git diff --check passed. Prior manual isolated temp smoke remains /tmp/tmp.TlcR1qJCP0/work/.agents/pm with research preset custom type create/list/health/validate successful."
  "2026-06-28T08:13:42.609Z",codex-gpt5,"Final review-cleanup evidence 2026-06-28 for PR #394: addressed CodeRabbit summary docstring-coverage warning by adding targeted docstrings to the SDK cloneOptionContracts helper and the new test requireOptionContract helper. This is comment-only for executable behavior; the prior full coverage run on the same code paths remains 257 files / 5139 tests / 100% statements, branches, functions, and lines, and GitHub coverage will re-run on the pushed head. Verification after docstring cleanup: focused tests node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/sdk/tool-option-contracts.spec.ts tests/unit/commands/contracts-command.spec.ts tests/unit/sdk/sdk-index.spec.ts passed 3 files / 148 tests; pnpm typecheck passed; pnpm lint passed with static quality gate passed; pnpm contracts:check passed; pnpm security:scan found no credential-like secrets; pnpm audit --audit-level moderate found no known vulnerabilities; git diff --check passed."
  "2026-06-28T08:22:35.177Z",codex-gpt5,"Review response 2026-06-28 for PR #394 Gemini test-state feedback: changed tests/unit/sdk/tool-option-contracts.spec.ts to prove exported contract object isolation with side-effect-free reference inequality assertions instead of mutating and restoring exported module state. Verification after the fix: focused tests node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/sdk/tool-option-contracts.spec.ts tests/unit/commands/contracts-command.spec.ts tests/unit/sdk/sdk-index.spec.ts passed 3 files / 148 tests; pnpm typecheck passed; pnpm lint passed with static quality gate passed and duplicate count unchanged at 26 known clones / 809 TS lines; pnpm contracts:check passed; pnpm security:scan found no credential-like secrets; pnpm audit --audit-level moderate found no known vulnerabilities; git diff --check passed."
  "2026-06-28T08:31:18.530Z",codex-gpt5,"Review response 2026-06-28 for PR #394 Gemini double-clone feedback: simplified TOOL_BASIC_ITEM_FILTER_OPTION_CONTRACTS to compose readonly base and relation contract groups directly, leaving cloning at exported array boundaries where mutable public ToolOptionFlagContract[] arrays are produced. Verification after the fix: focused tests node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/sdk/tool-option-contracts.spec.ts tests/unit/commands/contracts-command.spec.ts tests/unit/sdk/sdk-index.spec.ts passed 3 files / 148 tests; pnpm typecheck passed; pnpm lint passed with static quality gate passed and duplicate count unchanged at 26 known clones / 809 TS lines; pnpm contracts:check passed; pnpm security:scan found no credential-like secrets; pnpm audit --audit-level moderate found no known vulnerabilities; git diff --check passed."
  "2026-06-28T11:43:51.127Z",claude-code-agent,"Implementation start: continuing active pm SDK/CLI work after duplicate-safe all-status search and GitHub sweep. No open PRs; GitHub issue #374 remains externally blocked on missing RELEASE_PAT; Dependabot, code-scanning, and secret-scanning alerts are empty; pnpm audit is clean. Reusing pm-92if plus release-health pm-7zs0 instead of creating duplicate items."
  "2026-06-28T12:06:18.554Z",claude-code-agent,"Evidence: shared list/search item filter option contracts extracted into src/cli/commands/item-filter-options.ts, with list/search option interfaces now reusing the same command-local SDK/package-facing shape. Stabilized the MCP compact-output integration test under full coverage load with a 60s timeout. Verification passed: pnpm build; full coverage node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage = 257 files / 5139 tests / 100% statements, branches, functions, and lines; pm test pm-92if --run --progress passed 17/17 linked checks; focused list/search/contracts/SDK suite passed; pnpm contracts:check; pnpm changelog:pm:check using pm-changelog 2026.6.27 with CHANGELOG.md unchanged item_count=1363; package doctor deep ok; pm health summary ok; history drift ok with only existing resolution metadata warning backlog validate_resolution_missing_fields:258; git diff --check passed. Manual temp smoke at /tmp/tmp.64AMBk8DSx used isolated PM_PATH/PM_GLOBAL_PATH and passed init with research type preset, custom Experiment type storage, Task/Experiment create, list/search shared filters, health, and validate. GitHub sweep found no open PRs, issue #374 remains external RELEASE_PAT config, no Dependabot/code-scanning/secret-scanning alerts, pnpm audit clean. Sentry CLI returned recent scrubbed unresolved issue records and sentry-telemetry gate reported critical=0 high=0 telemetry finish_error_rate_pct=0.76."
  "2026-06-29T07:22:36.340Z",claude-code-agent,"Evidence: GitHub sweep found open Dependabot PR #398 (actions/cache 6.1.0) and #399 (@types/node 26.0.1), no open Dependabot/code-scanning alerts, pnpm audit --audit-level moderate clean. This branch bundles both reports: @types/node 26.0.1 in package.json/pnpm-lock.yaml and actions/cache pinned to 55cc8345863c7cc4c66a329aec7e433d2d1c52a9 with v6.1.0 comments across CI/release/nightly workflows. Verification passed: pnpm install --frozen-lockfile with repo store, focused workflow+SDK tests 118/118, pnpm build, pnpm typecheck, pnpm lint, pnpm quality:static, pnpm contracts:check, pnpm audit, pnpm security:scan, package doctor deep ok, node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage 258 files / 5147 tests / 100/100/100/100, pnpm changelog:pm:check unchanged after regeneration, Sentry/telemetry gate ok critical=0 high=0 telemetry_finish_error_rate_pct=0.74 failures_without_error_code_rows=0, temp smoke /tmp/tmp.994k5jbTjP passed lifecycle + package scaffold/install/doctor/command/typecheck/test."
  "2026-06-29T07:36:17.369Z",claude-code-agent,"Review resolution: accepted CodeRabbit finding on PR #400 that @types/node@26 was ahead of package engines.node >=22.18.0 and the Node 22 CI smoke. Adjusted package.json to @types/node ^22.20.0 and regenerated pnpm-lock.yaml with @types/node 22.20.0 / undici-types 6.21.0, preserving the supported runtime floor instead of raising it. Validation after fix: pnpm typecheck; node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/integration/ci-workflow-contract.spec.ts tests/unit/sdk/sdk-index.spec.ts; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage => 258 files, 5147 tests, 100/100/100/100 coverage."
  "2026-06-29T07:49:28.134Z",claude-code-agent,"Correction: earlier file notes and evidence referenced accepting Dependabot PR #399 as @types/node 26.0.1. Current PR #400 head 12bd005 intentionally does not adopt Node 26 types because engines.node and CI keep Node 22 support. Final state is package.json @types/node ^22.20.0 and pnpm-lock.yaml @types/node 22.20.0 / undici-types 6.21.0."
  "2026-06-29T08:04:33.306Z",claude-code-agent,"Evidence: addressed PR #400 cubic P3 linked-test history feedback. Implemented opt-in skipNoop handling in mutateItem and enabled it for pm test add/remove so duplicate linked-test adds and non-matching removes return changed=false without appending no-op tests_add history, while plan/update callers retain existing empty changedFields behavior. Validation: pnpm typecheck; pnpm quality:static; pnpm contracts:check; git diff --check; node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/commands/plan-command.spec.ts; node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/commands/test-command.spec.ts; node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/core/store/item-store.spec.ts; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage => 258 files, 5147 tests, coverage 100/100/100/100. Manual temp smoke in /tmp/pm-cli-smoke-lodyS9 used built dist CLI with sandboxed PM_GLOBAL_PATH: duplicate add changed=false, history lines 2->2, linked run passed."
  "2026-06-29T08:20:33.941Z",claude-code-agent,"Review response evidence: addressed latest PR #400 Gemini/cubic feedback. Moved opt-in skipNoop no-op return before history-stream policy enforcement so duplicate linked-test no-ops do not auto-create or fail on missing history streams; omitted historyPolicy warnings from no-op returns because no history policy is enforced when no history row will be written. Replaced stale package.json/pnpm-lock.yaml file notes so pm-92if now records @types/node ^22.20.0 / 22.20.0 and undici-types 6.21.0 for the Node 22 support floor. Added regression coverage for duplicate linked-test no-op behavior under strict missing-stream policy. Validation: focused plan/test/item-store suites passed (test-command now 54 tests); pnpm typecheck; pnpm quality:static; pnpm contracts:check; git diff --check; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage => 258 files, 5148 tests, 100/100/100/100; pnpm security:scan no secrets; pnpm audit --audit-level moderate no vulnerabilities; manual temp smoke /tmp/pm-cli-smoke-bFfolD duplicate changed=false, history 2->2, linked run passed."
